====introduction====
jquery is a library of javascript 

====selection===
$ => is a superglobal object 
$('tag');  select an element with tag 
$('.class'); select an element with it's class
$('#id');    select an element with it's unique id 
=====jQuery API====


=====changing DOM element css classes ====
selected_element.toggleClass("classname");=> to add or remove class to selected elment 

selected_element.next(); => to get the next sibling of the current element 


========change attributes and set attributes==========

selected_element.attr("attributename", "value"); => to change the attribute value and to put attribue if it isn't found 

=========poroparty and value using css=====
selected_element.css(proparty,value); => to set the value to the probarty

selected_element.css(proparty); => to get the value from the probarty

==========inside <tag>??????</tag> mean contant of tag==========

Selected_element.val(); => get the value of some form elemnt such as input ,select,textarea 

Selected_element.val(value); => put the value to  some form elemnt such as input ,select,textarea 

Selected_element.html(); => to get the content of the selected element in the form of html mean tags links and so on  NOte: used only in html not xml 

Selected_element.html(value); => to put value in the placeholder of the selected tag  e.g <p>Here</P>

Selected_element.text(); => to get the content of the selected element and all decendants with the form of text not without it's tags unlike the [.html() method] Note:used in both html and xml document 

=======deleting a DOM element=========
Selected_element.remove(filter); => delete the selected element with the specific filter 

======adding a DOM element ========
selected_element.append("element"); => append the element as a last child to the selected_element

selected_element.prepend("element"); => append the element before the selected_element 

element.insertBefore(target); => insert the element before the target 
 


 







